<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>PvP Server Killing</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Antwon">Antwon</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:18 a.m. 1/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> PvP Server Killing<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Hello all,

<P>I have been playing the PvP server and this past weekend I did a fair amount of player killing. (About 20 kills probably)
<P>I like the level restriction and if anything I realized that even within the level limits if you attack someone 2 or more levels below you, they have almost no chance. As much as I love pking, removing the level restrictions would be stupid since it would just result in high level characters killing people who have absolutely no prayer of fighting back.
<P>My other point is that I seemed to surprise alot of the good races I killed. I play a DE Necro and I do not kill any evil races, although I kill the good races.
<P>Why were people so surprised I was killing them? Is there some sort of etiquette that has been enforced on the PvP server I was not made aware of? I was under the impression good and evil were constantly killing each other, yet I was given responses that only me and a few of my friends were doing the killing.
<P>What is going on in the PvP server? Is it race war or not? Or has the PvP server become like all other online games where it is simply personal battles regardless of race?
<P>Antwon
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
